Description: Bead, pendant, necklace (?); a collection of sixty-four blue-green glazed composition pendant beads of various shapes and dimensions; nine lotus pendants, with suspension loops at top and base; nine pendants in form of plumed cartouches, two with one inscription and seven with another, with suspension loops at top and base; seventeen pendants in form of rearing uraeus crowned with solar disc (two incomplete); eight pendants in form of hes-vase with suspension loops at top and base (one incomplete); five poppy-head pendants with suspension loops at top and base; three mandrake pendants with suspension loops at top and base; two date pendants with suspension loops at top and base; eight pear-shaped pendants with suspension loops at top and base (one incomplete).
Curator's comments: Published: Andrews, Amulets of Ancient Egypt (1994): fig.65
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Louis, Duc de Blacas d'Aulps
Previous owner: Previous owner/ex-collection: Louis, Duc de Blacas d'Aulps
